i have an area of m x m that require screeding to about thick how much should it cost the screeding will be to cover under floor heating pipes in a conservatory hi i had some screeding done done by a cowboy he charged drank gallons of tea and made a terrible job of it every bit of furniture we put on it wobbled it was all bumps valleys and after a week cracks he refused to come back and even look at it i had to hire a mini skip and take the whole lot up then i got a proper builder in he spent a full day setting out wooden frames and getting everything level the next day he arrived with a mate and they laid the floor in a morning it was level dead level he charged me so a job that should have cost actually cost an extra plus for the mini skip good luck with your builder i hope you get the right job done first time around Chatsworth House Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Poker jargon Knots Landing Basement Japanese tea ceremony Welding President (game) Brewery 2000 Australian Grand Prix Mattress Dairy IPod Upholstery Seismic retrofit Plastic Sand casting Bicycle frame Equine conformation Deck (ship) Wood Social rule Leather Collapse of the World Trade Center RuneScape quests Piano Coffee Radio controlled airplane Characters in the Smurfs Aerial (dance move) Heinkel He 112 Motorcycle USS Anderson (DD-411) Hamster American and British English differences Strake Eifel Aqueduct Construction Sento Drill bit USS Ammen (DD-527) Son Goku (Dragon Ball) Tesla coil USS Yorktown (CV-10) Firefighter Bubble Bobble Solar cell Volleyball Hal Trosky Unemployment Industrial Workers of the World USS Waters (DD-115) Avenue Q Geodesic dome R46 (New York City Subway car) Universal Serial Bus MapleStory Donald Neilson CPU design Cocaine Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Massachusetts Bay Transportation Authority Textile manufacturing Gramophone record M16 (rifle) Internal ballistics Dundas Square Kimono Handloading RISC IPod nano New York Giants Ocean thermal energy 